Docker Compose (see Getting Started)"},"276":{"id":"/docs/faq-28","page_id":"/docs/faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#how-do-i-get-started","content":"Install the mobile APK"},"277":{"id":"/docs/faq-29","page_id":"/docs/faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#how-do-i-get-started","content":"Connect the mobile app to your server URL"},"278":{"id":"/docs/faq-30","page_id":"/docs/faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#do-i-need-ai-api-keys","content":"AI features (auto-tagging, auto-summary, bot replies) are optional. They require configuring an AI provider (OpenAI-compatible or Anthropic) in the admin dashboard. Without AI, all core features work normally."},"279":{"id":"/docs/faq-31","page_id":"/docs/faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#what-are-the-minimum-server-requirements","content":"1 CPU core, 512MB RAM, 10GB storage"},"280":{"id":"/docs/faq-32","page_id":"/docs/faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#what-are-the-minimum-server-requirements","content":"Docker and Docker Compose"},"281":{"id":"/docs/faq-33","page_id":"/docs/faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#what-are-the-minimum-server-requirements","content":"PostgreSQL-compatible environment (pgvector extension auto-installed via Docker)"},"282":{"id":"/docs/faq-34","page_id":"/docs/faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#where-is-my-data-stored","content":"On your own server. All data (notes, images, videos) stays on hardware you control. Storage can be local disk or Cloudflare R2 (S3-compatible)."},"283":{"id":"/docs/faq-35","page_id":"/docs/faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#can-i-export-my-data","content":"The API allows fetching all memos, diaries, and resources via standard REST endpoints. The admin dashboard also provides health and stats visibility."},"284":{"id":"/docs/faq-36","page_id":"/docs/faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#is-data-encrypted","content":"**In transit**: Yes, if you configure HTTPS via a reverse proxy (see Deployment Guide)"},"285":{"id":"/docs/faq-37","page_id":"/docs/faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#is-data-encrypted","content":"**At rest**: Database-level encryption depends on your PostgreSQL setup. File storage is as-is on disk/R2"},"286":{"id":"/docs/faq-38","page_id":"/docs/faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#is-data-encrypted","content":"**Passwords**: Hashed with bcrypt"},"287":{"id":"/docs/faq-39","page_id":"/docs/faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#does-mosaic-support-multiple-users","content":"Currently, Mosaic is designed for single-user or small-team use. Multiple users share the same server instance."},"288":{"id":"/docs/faq-40","page_id":"/docs/faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#can-i-use-mosaic-offline","content":"The mobile app caches data locally using SQLite. You can view and edit notes offline — they sync when you reconnect to the server."},"289":{"id":"/docs/faq-41","page_id":"/docs/faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#what-ai-models-are-supported","content":"Any OpenAI-compatible API or Anthropic API. This includes OpenAI (GPT-4, GPT-4o), Anthropic (Claude), Ollama (local), and any provider offering compatible endpoints."},"290":{"id":"/docs/faq-42","page_id":"/docs/faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#how-does-sync-work","content":"Mosaic uses a timestamp-based cursor protocol. Each entity type (memos, diaries, resources, bots) tracks its last update time. The mobile client pulls changes since its last sync cursor and merges them locally."},"291":{"id":"/docs/faq-43","page_id":"/docs/faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#what-happens-if-theres-a-conflict","content":"Mosaic follows a \"last-writer-wins\" strategy based on the `updated_at` timestamp. The most recent change is kept."},"292":{"id":"/docs/faq-44","page_id":"/docs/faq","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/faq#the-server-wont-start","content":"Check that PostgreSQL is running and reachable"},"293":{"id":"/docs/fa